TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hafer, Catherine
T1  - On the Origins of Property Rights: Conflict and Productionin the State of Nature
PY  - 2006
Y1  - 2006/01/01
DO  - 10.1111/j.1467-937X.2006.00371.x
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 73
IS  - 1
SP  - 119
EP  - 143
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - I analyse the emergence of property rights in a model of conflict and production in the absence of institutions of enforcement. The population of agents evolves dynamically through conflicts for possession of factor goods among pairs of randomly matched agents. Conflicts are incomplete information wars of attrition with an agent's type consisting of his or her independently drawn valuation of the prize and cost of competing for it. I prove equilibrium existence and show that in the steady state of the game, the population sorts into two stable groups (resource “haves” and “have-nots”) in accordance with a known function of their primitive types.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-937X.2006.00371.x
ER  - 



